29/04/2005
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- Nebojsa Pavkovic, the former chief of staff of the Yugoslav Army, appeared before the UN war crimes tribunal on Thursday (28 April) to plead not guilty to four counts of crimes against humanity and one count of violations of the laws or customs of war, including deportation, murder and persecution.
He surrendered to the court on Monday.
Pavkovic was indicted with three other generals, Vladimir Lazarevic, Sreten Lukic and Vlastimir Djordjevic.
No trial date has been set.
(Reuters, BBC - 28/04/05)
